    solution_text_english: "Saturated Carbon Compounds:\n1. Only single bonds between carbon atoms (C-C)\n2. General formula: CₙH₂ₙ₊₂ (Alkanes)\n3. Maximum number of hydrogen atoms\n4. More stable\n5. Less reactive\n\nExamples:\n- Methane: CH₄\n- Ethane: C₂H₆ (H₃C-CH₃)\n- Propane: C₃H₈\n\nUnsaturated Carbon Compounds:\n1. Double (C=C) or triple bonds (C≡C) between carbons\n2. General formula: CₙH₂ₙ (Alkenes), CₙH₂ₙ₋₂ (Alkynes)\n3. Lesser number of hydrogen atoms\n4. Less stable\n5. More reactive\n\nExamples:\n- Ethene: C₂H₄ (H₂C=CH₂)\n- Ethyne: C₂H₂ (HC≡CH)\n- Propene: C₃H₆\n\nTest: Bromine water - unsaturated compounds decolourise it.",
