    solution_text_english: "Mirror Formula:\n\n1/f = 1/v + 1/u\n\nWhere:\n\nf = Focal length\n- Distance from pole to principal focus\n- Concave mirror: Negative (-)\n- Convex mirror: Positive (+)\n\nv = Image distance\n- Distance from pole to image\n- Real image: Negative (-)\n- Virtual image: Positive (+)\n\nu = Object distance\n- Distance from pole to object\n- Always negative (-)\n- Object always on left side\n\nMagnification:\nm = -v/u = h'/h\n\nWhere:\nh' = Image height\nh = Object height\n\nSign Convention:\n- Left of mirror: Negative\n- Right of mirror: Positive\n- Above principal axis: Positive\n- Below principal axis: Negative",
